The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Rejig at Hyderabad Industries

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, April 4: Hyderabad Industries has decided to transfer its heavy engineering division at Uttarpara to Titagarh Wagons Limited. 

 Hyderabad Industries, a CK Birla group company, wanted to exit from non-core activities while focusing on the core business of building products, a company release said.

 The heavy engineering division manufactures products such as excavators, cranes and steel structures. It also specialises in equipment for mining and power generation. 

 The deal is subject to the approval of shareholders of Hyderabad Industries and creditors. 

 Hyderabad Industries has a turnover of Rs 400 crore. 




